In Bach's time, there were no world tours.
Beethoven, Brahms, Bartok, Enescu were working people, who were artists and not sales representatives.
To me, touring, festivals, concerts, album releases, all of that is great, extraordinary, but only if it's done in the service of music.
If not, we're in a system where creativity suffers, it's not free.
To illustrate this phenomenon, David Grimal gave an example of Romanian products before and after joining the European Union: "In Romania, before joining the EU, you had good vegetables and meat".
