The rare disease that a man suffers from
American Nick Hess was suspected by his family of being an alcoholic, his wife even filming him when he was drunk, he could barely stand on his feet and his words were hard to understand.
Although the 35-year-old man said he had not consumed alcohol, he was clearly intoxicated.
When she first accused me of being drunk, without drinking, I thought she was crazy.
"But friends and family thought 'maybe he drinks alone, he's a secret alcoholic,'" he says, according to the Mirror.
When he saw the footage of his wife with him, the man from Columbus, Ohio, just didn't recognize himself: "I was looking into my eyes and I wasn't there".
'It was awful, I couldn't remember anything.'
In addition, his wife, who, though doubting him for a while, eventually went with him to countless doctors, remembers that Nick's breath smelled of alcohol.
The moment that put Nick on his mind most was when, after a minor accident, when he was hit by another car, it was discovered that he had a blood alcohol level three times the legal limit, even though the night before he had only had one beer.
After years and countless investigations, it was discovered that Nick suffered from an extremely rare disease, "Auto-brewery syndrome".
Basically, his body causes all the carbohydrates he consumes to ferment into alcohol.
The one who suspected that this might be Nick's disease was his own wife.
There's no cure yet, but since he gave up carbs, Nick hasn't had an episode like this.
